try:
		system.tag.writeBlocking(["[.]../TestTag"], ['previousValue.value: {}, currentValue.value: {}'.format(previousValue.value,currentValue.value)])
		if (previousValue.value == 0 and currentValue.value == 1):
			if system.tag.readBlocking(["[.]/InProcess"])[0].value == 1:
				DataAccess.Log.LogError("Already in progress") 
			else:
				paths = system.tag.readBlocking(["[.]../Inputs/PathRESP", "[.]../Inputs/PathRSD"])
				system.tag.writeBlocking([paths[0].value, paths[1].value, "[.]/InProcess"], [0, 0, 1])
				baseTagPath = tagPath[:-len('/Status/Trigger')]
				tagParams = system.tag.getConfiguration(baseTagPath)[0]['parameters']
				function = str(tagParams['Function'].value)
			
				def execFunction(function, baseTagPath):
					exec(function+"(baseTagPath)")
					
				# Test that we can reference the function before we call it asynchronously to catch the error here - CMB 20231020
				testCode = 'functionRef = ' + function
				exec(testCode)
				
				pNumber = system.tag.readBlocking("[.]../Parameters.ProcessStep")[0].value
				# Invoke Asynchronous function call - PCM 20230510
				system.util.invokeAsynchronous(function=execFunction, args=[function, baseTagPath], description=str(pNumber) + ' - ' + function)
	except Exception as e:
		# Write trigger back low, log error - PCM
		# Modified to log without using DataAccess and reset InProcess - CMB 20231020
		system.tag.writeBlocking(['[.]Trigger', '[.]InProcess'], [0, 0])
		logger = system.util.getLogger('transitionTriggerTag')
		logger.error(' | '.join([tagPath, 'MES', repr(e)]))

- Handshake Signals
	- Signals: 
		- Ready to send (RTS) (sender->receiver)

		- Receiver reads data and copies it out of tag structure
		- Receiver updates response data
		- Receiver sets RSD tag
		- Sender reads response and copies it out of tag structure
		- Sender clears RTS tag
		- Receiver clears RSD tag
